					<p>
						Many chronic health problems, such as diabetes, obesity, hypertension, and heart disease, can be prevented or reversed through changes in lifestyle. However, often this message does not reach individuals who do not visit their doctor regularly. Mobile health brings education directly into neighborhoods where people live, play, and call home. The Steps of Success (SOS) Mobile Health Adult Support program, an empowerment training series educating families about chronic illness management, nutrition, physical fitness, and related factors, was developed to increase overall health awareness and empower families to make informed decisions for healthy lifestyles. The Teen Support Program is comprised of 30 weekly supportive training sessions, which teach ‘Steps of Success’ for positive social and emotional development. These peer interaction initiatives, beyond increasing self-esteem, provide opportunities for self-expression, social interaction, expanded community exposure, and a trustworthy space for support, encouragement, and increased self-worth. Last year, 40 adults and teens received services through these programs. The goal is to continually increase that number through outreach and promotion, using the Mobile Health Unit as a rolling billboard for preventive care.  
